==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kamala
<hw>Ka*ma"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The
red dusty hairs of the capsules of an East Indian tree (<spn>Mallotus
Philippinensis</spn>) used for dyeing silk. It is violently emetic, and
is used in the treatment of tapeworm.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>kameela</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kame</ent>⟦br⟧
